Package: ihazr
Title: Survival Data Visualization and Non-Parametric Hazard Estimation using D3
Version: 0.1.0
Date: 2018-10-31
Authors@R: c(
    person("C. Jason", "Liang", , "liangcj@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Kyle", "Webb", , "kylepwebb1992@gmail.com", role = "aut"))
Description: ihazr stands for Interactive Hazard Regression. 
    This package enables the user to invetigate their data through the htmlwidgets 
    package and JavaScript D3.js. The user can create scatterplots and cumulative hazarad 
    plots for their survival data over all covariates of interest.
    A nonparametric hazard estimation is also plotted and bandwidth can be 
    changed for the Epinechnikov kernel. 
    The ihazr package is a useful tool for any sort of preliminary survival 
    analysis and estimation. 
BugReports: https://github.com/liangcj/ihazr/issues
Depends: R (>= 3.2.0)
License: GPL-2
Imports: htmlwidgets (>= 0.8)
Suggests: dplyr (>= 0.7.5), 
          shiny (>= 1.0.0),
          survival (>= 2.42)
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 6.1.0
